text:
Karin Dor (Kätherose Derr; 22 February 1938 – 6 November 2017) was a German actress. She was born in Wiesbaden, Germany. She starred in the James Bond movie "You Only Live Twice" and the Alfred Hitchcock movie "Topaz".
Dor died at a nursing home in Munich, Germany on 6 November 2017 at the age of 79.
